author: sina.com.cn
title: 【战新产业"百大工程"】国投聚焦生物育种产业，一体化布局种业能力建设|国投_新浪财经_新浪网
text:
转自：国家开发投资集团有限公司
当前，面对世界百年未有之大变局加速演进，提升我国生物育种产业链供应链韧性和安全水平具有重要战略意义。国投充分发挥中央企业市场需求、集成创新、组织平台等优势，聚焦生物育种产业，一体化布局种业能力建设，锻长板、补短板、强基础，勇做科技创新的排头兵，加快建设现代化产业体系。
经过多年努力，我国在生物技术领域取得一系列重要突破，推动了生物育种技术的进步。在国家的大力支持下，生物育种产业链供应链正在重塑，不稳定性不确定性明显增加。在此背景下，国投积极响应国家粮食产业链供应链安全要求，发挥中央企业“稳定器、压舱石”作用，以国务院国资委战 新产业 “百大工程”“生物育种产业能力提升项目示范工程”项目为牵引，打造种业科技领军企业，培育行业新质生产力，构建以生物育种为核心、“研育繁推服”产业链一体化布局的种业生态。
发展新质生产力，全方位优化布局产业链
2023年9月注资40亿，在三亚设立国投种业科技有限公司，作为国投集团生物育种产业科技运营管理平台。国投种业自成立以来，便明确战略定位。依托 国投资本 优势和资源优势，聚焦生物育种核心技术，推动种业产业的创新升级和可持续发展。通过优化投资布局、加强技术研发、引进高端人才等，全面提升公司在生物育种领域的核心竞争力。目前已完成对种业上市公司—— 丰乐种业 的并购工作，并通过丰乐种业进一步加强对生物育种产业及种业上下游产业链的深度布局，2024年内完成在数字农业、生物技术领域多家并购。国投种业对投资企业积极赋能，并购丰乐种业后，2024年丰乐种业玉米种子国内市场占有率预计达到2.6%，较2023年提高占比0.5%。2024年前9月，国投种业实现营业收入9.04亿元，资产总额44.77亿元，累计投入研发费用7237.83万元。
科技引领发展，建设自主研发体系
以科技创新为引领，探索“科研、产业和资本融合发展”的合作模式，助力关键核心技术转化孵化，实现互利共赢和高质量发展。国投投资布局国内主要性状公司，实现对国内性状公司和主要科学家的广泛覆盖，2024年使用上述公司玉米转基因性状的审定品种达到已审品种的90%以上；国投同崖州湾国家实验室签订战略合作协议，对李家洋院士研发的双季早粳稻首台套——“中科发早粳”进行商业化推广。在科技攻关方面，国投种业协调丰乐种业牵头承担科技创新2030-农业生物育种重大项目，隆平生物、杭州瑞丰、华中农大等十几家单位参与，共同负责超高产耐逆玉米新品种设计与培育项目，已收到中央经费4350万元；成立科创中心，以专业化科技运营管理机构推动科研工作平稳有序开展。科创中心以构建“种质资源+数据信息”为基础、市场需求为导向的一体化育种创新体系为目标，抓牢顶层设计、资源整合、研发管理、基础攻关四个方向，上游与科研院所紧密合作，下游赋能性状公司和种业公司两大业务主体，自身作为引擎驱动国投种业自主研发体系蓬勃发展。
有效整合产业资源，加强央地合作
国投不断整合产业资源，加强央地合作，以获取优质制种基地及种子产业互联平台研发、运营为发力点，持续加强与张掖市政府的合作力度。与张掖市合资设立公司，专项推进高标准制种基地建设。在甘州区沙井镇兴隆村打造1400亩智慧制种示范基地，打造“基础数据一个库、农情监测一张网、农作处方一套图”，通过精准化、智能化、规划化、标准化、数字化制种示范，引领玉米制种产业向高质量现代化发展。目前数字化综合服务平台上线甘州区全部57家制种企业，已完成备案土地约70万亩，备案品种704个，同时，为3家代表性制种企业11万亩土地，提供免费生产管理服务，以交易为核心功能的项目二期科技攻关已签署合同，正在加紧开发。目前，国投种业在张掖市总计运营超5万亩核心制种基地，完成制种生产管理信息化系统的开发并覆盖超10万亩核心制种基地，实现以数据驱动生产管理决策，有效实现传统产业与新兴产业协同发展以推动形成新质生产力。
引领产业发展，社会效益经济效益双丰收
国投聚焦主责主业，围绕生物育种产业重点领域、重要技术，利用产业基金具有天然的触角、探头、孵化作用，一体化布局建设种业产业链。国投种业通过加强生物育种技术的研发和应用，实现种业科技自立自强、种源自主可控；通过集中整合优质产业资源，充实高质高产优质新品种，支持国家农业发展战略，提高粮食国内生产供给水平，确保国内粮食供应安全稳定。下一步，国投种业将持续深度融合生物技术、信息技术和数字技术，以新技术赋能种子产业，推动生物育种产业结构创新升级。优化种子营销、服务体系，大力推广良种良法配套应用，促进种业产业结构升级。创新种业知识产权运营模式，开放赋能中小种企，带动生物育种产业链相关板块协同发展，共同提升生物育种产业整体竞争力。
【责任编辑：张任田慧】

author: 那菲
title: 致敬風雨中最溫暖力量！黃敏惠慰勉第一線工程、清潔隊員
text:
嘉義120年來首次遭遇颱風登陸，嘉義市民生基礎設施損毀，市容景觀一夕間遭遇重創，市區多處主要幹道因路樹倒伏而影響通行。嘉義市長黃敏惠今（10）日一早偕同市府秘書長陳永豐前往各清理作業現場，包括文化公園、大雅路一段、興嘉公園、北香湖公園，隨後前往底渣再利用廠，逐一慰勞奮戰多日、來自各縣市的工程人員以及面對災後龐大垃圾清運量的清潔隊員，感謝他們頂著連日風雨、堅守崗位，搶進工程進度，讓城市能早日恢復日常，黃敏惠市長也特別叮囑全體工程、清潔人員在執行勤務時務必注意自身安全。歷經中央及各縣市政府連日努力及支援後，嘉義市全市主要幹道已於昨日全面恢復通行。
黃敏惠提到，颱風丹娜絲路徑百年一遇，對嘉義市造成相當大的衝擊，市府團隊全力投入應對風災，也針對各縣市調派人力、機具以及車輛支援，大幅推進搶修進度表示感謝。同時，這次風災造成大量招牌及看板損毀、路樹倒伏，面對災後龐大的垃圾清運量，嘉義市府自7月8日下午2時起，動員比平時多3倍人力，收運垃圾加班至淩晨1時，車輛出勤次數比平日增加3倍，當日收運垃圾達936公噸，較平日200餘公噸收運垃圾量增加近5倍。
精選報導：扯！栗正傑稱颱風闖賴清德本命區是「天公伯來收你了」 軍方人士：冷血
黃敏惠對全體清潔隊員表示感謝，即使面對高強度、高密度的作業需求，依然秉持使命感，堅持完成每一個清理環節，展現嘉義市團隊精神與公務效率。並感謝所有工程人員、清潔隊員與每位市民攜手守護家園，展現風雨中的人情溫暖與城市的韌性。
市府建設處表示「在市府團隊與中央、各縣市支援全力搶修下，已於 7月9日完成嘉義全市11條主要幹道、15個路段搶通，接下來將搶進各重點公園，進行園內便道樹幹及樹枝清運，讓機具設備可通行使用，下一階段再進行逐步復原。接下來將搶進各重點公園，進行園內便道樹幹及樹枝清運，讓機具設備可通行使用，下一階段再進行逐步復原。也呼籲市民朋友近期因救災作業，將持續封閉公園，請市民暫時避免前往相關區域，以維護自身安全。」

author: Mary Walrath-Holdridge
title: Kathleen Wilson's Minnesota dentist did 30 procedures at once: lawsuit
text: 20 fillings, 4 root canals, 8 crowns in one visit add up to lawsuit for Minnesota dentist [Mary Walrath-Holdridge](https://www.usatoday.com/staff/12093029002/mary-walrathholdridge/) A Minnesota dentist has become the subject of a malpractice lawsuit after his patient accused him of "disfiguring" her. The civil lawsuit was filed in Hennepin County, Minnesota last week by Kathleen Wilson, who alleged Dr. Kevin Molldrem and [Molldrem Family Dentistry](https://molldremdentistry.com/) caused her significant injury that is still being corrected. According to the suit, Molldrem performed more than 30 producers on Wilson in a single July 2020 visit, doing eight crowns, four root canals and 20 fillings in one go. The lawsuit alleges that the dentist "perform[ed] this work improperly," resulting in pain and suffering, embarrassment, emotional distress, and disfigurement. Molldrem was likewise accused of using improper levels of anesthesia during the procedures and falsifying medical records to cover it up. Treatment called 'inconceivable' “It is inconceivable that Dr. Molldrem could have prepared and placed 8 crowns under these circumstances in the time allotted, not to mention the additional 20 restorations,” wrote [Dr. Avrum Goldstein,](https://www.seakexperts.com/members/4827-avrum-r-goldstein) a dentist and expert witness brought on by Wilson's attorney, in an affidavit. Goldstein, who is a faculty member at [NOVA Southeastern University](https://dental.nova.edu/aboutus/faculty/goldstein-avrum%20.html?_gl=1*1kqtqxq*_gcl_au*ODA4NzUxNTA1LjE3MDM3OTc5MjI.), also wrote that Wilson had been correctly diagnosed as having a "rare condition" causing decay in almost all of her teeth, but Mollderm's course of action was not a proper form of treatment. "[Wilson’s] required a slow, thoughtful, careful and measured response to her disease,” he said in his report. “Trying to fill every hole in every tooth in her mouth in one visit is not only the antithesis of what was indicated, it is not humanly possible to achieve in an effective or constructive manner.” Doctors remove wrong organ from man: [They opened him up to remove his appendix. They mistakenly took out much more, lawsuit says.](/story/news/health/2023/11/07/doctors-accidentally-remove-wrong-organ-surgery/71487292007/) The lawsuit also accused Mollderm of tampering with medical records to falsify the amount of anesthesia that was reportedly used, which in reality was nearly double the standard number of units, according to court paperwork. According to Goldstein, the maximum dose of anesthesia given in three hours should not exceed 490 mg, but Molldrem's records show he gave Wilson 960 mg. “Any negative cardiovascular or central nervous system outcomes could be tied to the local anesthetic overdose," he wrote. Wilson said in the suit that she has since had to have the dental work completely redone by other dentists to repair Molldrem’s “negligent work," an ongoing process that has caused her to lose income and rack up medical bills on top of enduring pain, suffering and embarrassment. She is seeking more than $50,000 in damages. Wilson's attorney and Molldrem did not immediately respond to request for comment.

author: cue
title: Arsenal miss out on top spot after 2-0 defeat by West Ham | The Straits Times
text:
LONDON - Misfiring Arsenal spurned the opportunity to reclaim first place in the Premier League as they lost 2-0 to spirited fellow Londoners West Ham United at the Emirates on Thursday.
West Ham only had three efforts on target but Tomas Soucek gave them a halftime lead before former Arsenal defender Konstantinos Mavropanos extended the advantage after the break.
Arsenal had more than twice as many chances but failed to take any as the visitors defended gamely.
Second-placed Arsenal remain on 40 points, two behind Liverpool who beat Burnley 2-0 on Tuesday.
"This is a very disappointing night for us," Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta told reporters. "We have to put the ball in (the net) and win it (the game)."
West Ham took the lead against the run of play after 13 minutes when Soucek netted after a pull-back from Jarrod Bowen who looked as if he just managed to keep the ball in play.
"It's difficult because the ball was in the air," Bowen told Amazon Prime. "It was hard to tell. It would have been easier to tell if it had been on the ground."
ARSENAL BLITZ
After that it was an Arsenal blitz with Bukayo Saka hitting the post and Gabriel Jesus missing two good chances before Mavropanos scored his first league goal for the Hammers with a thumping header from a James Ward-Prowse corner in the 55th.
"I think the best moment to score my first goal for West Ham and in the Premier League," said Mavropanos. "We work a lot on the set-pieces, so it was great. It is an important win for everyone and for our boss. We are really happy."
West Ham could have made it three from three chances but Said Benrahma had a penalty saved by David Raya in added time after a foul by former West Ham captain Declan Rice.
The defeat raises familiar questions about Arsenal's title credentials. They led the league this time last year only to falter in the run in and be overtaken by Manchester City.
It may have been one of those nights when things just did not happen in front of goal but finishing remains an issue.
As well as striking the post, Saka also had a near point-blank header stopped by Alphonse Areola, who made a string of fine saves in the second half too.
Jesus should have a scored when Arsenal were still one goal behind but headed over an open goal while fellow Brazilian Gabriel Martinelli also missed good opportunities.
The win leaves West Ham in sixth place on 33 points and marked a landmark night for their manager David Moyes who had never won at Arsenal in the league in 22 attempts. REUTERS
